{
  "text": "As it is mentioned in the introduction, any comparability graph is word-representable [CITATION_1] , and any odd cycle of length 5 or more, being a non-comparability graph, is word-representable [CITATION_2] . Moreover, odd wheels on six or more vertices are non-word-representable [CITATION_3] , and the set of 1 k -representable graphs, for any k \u2265 3, coincides with the set of all graphs by Theorem 1. Our next result shows that any 12-representable graph is necessarily a comparability graph.",
  "citation_candidates": [
